President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of North Dakota due to a severe winter storm and flooding that occurred from April 22 to May 25, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in various counties. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding. Alana B. Kuhn has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, with the possibility of additional designations in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.